gomodel:SYNGO_2621  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: \"Slitrk3 selectively induces functional inhibitory presynaptic differentiation in coculture\"\nFig.3: \"Slitrk3 knockdown decreases the density of inhibitory synapses in hippocampal culture\"\nFig.4: \"Slitrk3-/- mice have reduced inhibitory synapse density in CA1 region of hippocampus\"\nFig.5: \"Slitrk3-/- mice have reduced inhibitory synaptic transmission in CA1 of the hippocampus\". Experimental description: - \"Slitrk3 expressed in fibroblasts triggers only inhibitory presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons of cocultured rat hippocampal neurons. Recombinant Slitrk3 preferentially localizes to inhibitory postsynaptic sites.\"\n\n- Ephys is performed in WT and SLITRK3 KO mice.\n\n- \"The full-length cDNAs for mouse Slitrk1 (clone ID: mKIAA1910), Slitrk2 (40060548), Slitrk3 (6844461), Slitrk4 (40096585), Slitrk6 (4832410J21) and human PTPδ (40027582) were purchased from Kazusa DNA Research Institute, \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2621" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

